<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-112-204  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 112 204.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  March 13 1989 v11 n11 p28(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Glass becoming viable for hard drives: smaller drives make glassplatters more practical, observers say.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brownstein, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Industry observers say that glass disk platters may become asignificant technology for hard disk drives in the 1990s.andP;  Glassdisk platters were judged unsuitable for hard disk applications afew years ago, although the viability of glass is much bettertoday.andP;  There are several advantages to using glass.andP;  The glassplatter can be made with a smoother surface than is possible withaluminum, and the surface does not corrode.andP;  Glass does notrequire nickel plating before the magnetic media are applied, andthe glass surface is harder than aluminum surfaces, making it lessvulnerable to dents and penetration.andP;  Despite the advantages ofglass disk platters, there is still little demand for them.andP;  ArealTechnology Inc is the only company that has announced that it isdeveloping a glass disk.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TechnologyHard DiskDisk Drives.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>